last_episode_to_air.overview: Tabatha steps in to help a family-owned consignment store, where the husband-and-wife owners are at odds over how to make the store a success; tensions arise when a family member turns out to be a lackluster employee.

name: Relative Success with Tabatha
overview: Follow Australian hairstylist and salon owner Tabatha Coffey as she brings her expertise and personal experience to the complicated world of family businesses.

episodes.name: Drama, Italian Style
episodes.overview: Tabatha comes to the rescue of a family owned pizzeria, D'Amore's, where everyone is fighting over their piece of the pie. The owner, Joe D'Amore, has opened multiple locations of his east coast style restaurant across Southern California and after 30 years of hard work, he is considering a multi-million dollar offer to take the chain national. But Joe's children have other ideas in mind and are pushing back at him accepting the deal, leaving Joe stuck in the middle and unclear about which move to make.

episodes.name: The Family Stone
episodes.overview: Tabatha comes to the aid of a family owned jewelry company, Matthew's, and attempts to restore it to its glittering past. But with master diamond setter and owner, Michael Bogosian, having recently passed away, his sons and widow cannot agree on how to run things. If they can't get it together, this once dazzling business may lose its shine and close its doors for the last time.

episodes.name: Splitting at the Seams
episodes.overview: Family owned apparel company, NewMe, hopes to change the modest clothing scene, but without Tabathaâ€™s help, their family drama may jeopardize their dreams. The mother-daughter design duo is at odds with their son and brother turned business partner, causing tempers to fray.

episodes.name: In a Pickle
episodes.overview: A local deli in Long Beach, Calif., has a successful lunch service but faces a mountain of debt and a lack of leadership; Tabatha tries to change things before the doors close for good on the family business.

episodes.name: Spinning out of Control
episodes.overview: Sibling-owned fitness studio RPM seeks Tabatha's help to modernize its business model, but with one sister checked out and the other overwhelmed, the tension-filled family members risk losing their business and life savings.

episodes.name: Southern Dis-Comfort
episodes.overview: The children of the owner of Sweet Dixie Kitchen ask Tabatha to rein in their authoritarian mother and help repair the frayed family relations that threaten to blow up the business.

episodes.name: Getting Real-Estate
episodes.overview: A husband-and-wife business operating in the world's most exclusive zip code faces growing debt and mounting tensions; Tabatha works to get both the business and the couple's marriage back on a stable foundation.
